Help Type: topic
Topic: recipe

Workflow Recipe

Purpose:
  Read this after root help. It is the practical workflow guide for Agents operating `.wikg` archives.
  Use it to choose a starting point, interpret inspect output, answer questions from archive objects, and decide which topic to read next.

Operating rules:
  - Never unzip a `.wikg` archive, rewrite internal files, or bypass this CLI. Use CLI commands for archive edits.
  - Use Wiki Graph URIs as stable object handles.
  - If you have a URI and need valid operations, run `wikigraph <uri> --help`.
  - If you need concrete predicate usage for that URI type, run `wikigraph <uri> <predicate> --help`.
  - Never pass a bare filesystem path to URI-targeted commands.
    /Users/me/book.wikg -> wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg
    ./book.wikg -> wikg://book.wikg
  - Treat returned short URIs as archive-relative handles. Add the archive locator before passing them back:
    wikg://entity/Q8018 -> wikg:///absolute/path/book.wikg/entity/Q8018

Choose your starting point:
  - User gave you an existing `.wikg` archive:
    Inspect before searching, generating, or editing.
      wikigraph wikg://book.wikg inspect

  - User gave you source content and needs a reusable knowledge-base archive:
    Create or import a `.wikg` archive.
      wikigraph wikg://book.wikg create ./book.epub
      wikigraph wikg://notes.wikg create ./notes.md
      cat article.md | wikigraph wikg://article.wikg create --input-format markdown

  - User needs one-shot conversion without keeping an archive:
    Use transform.
      cat chapter.txt | wikigraph transform --input-format txt --output-format markdown

  - User needs a file projection from a ready archive:
    Export from the archive.
      wikigraph wikg://book.wikg export --output-format markdown --output out.md

After inspect:
  - If the archive is ready for retrieval, search a scope or open the URI that inspect suggests.
    wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg --query "恩典 婴儿洗礼"
    wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/chapter/3 --query "婴儿洗礼"

  - If inspect reports missing or unavailable index support, inspect the index target before building anything.
    wikigraph <archive-uri>/index --help
    wikigraph <archive-uri>/index build --help

  - If Reading Graph data is missing, chunk search, related expansion, and pack may be unavailable or incomplete.
    Inspect job help before starting generated work.
      wikigraph wikg://local/job --help
      wikigraph wikg://local/job add --help

  - If Knowledge Graph data is missing, entity and triple retrieval may be unavailable or incomplete.
    Knowledge Graph generation needs configuration and may require WikiSpine provider setup.
      wikigraph help config

  - If summaries are missing, summary reads and summary-based exports may be incomplete.
    Check the chapter or archive readiness before relying on summaries.

Answering questions:
  - Need document structure, chapter readiness, or chapter-local scope:
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chapter
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3

  - Need literal source wording or passages that mention a phrase:
    Start with source search from the narrowest useful scope.
      wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg --query "恩典 婴儿洗礼"
      wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/chapter/3 --query "婴儿洗礼"

  - Need source-backed passages and local reading context:
    Use chunk objects and evidence.
      wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chunk
      wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chunk/123 evidence

  - Need to understand a concept, person, place, term, or object:
    Use entity search, then ground or expand from the entity URI.
      wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/entity --query "朱元璋"
      wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/entity/Q8018
      wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/entity/Q8018 evidence
      wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/entity/Q8018 related --query "aspect"
    Do not use label text search as the primary path for known entities; aliases, translations, and variants may not match the label.

  - Need to trace a relation, claim, or subject-predicate-object connection:
    Use triple objects and evidence.
      wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/triple/Q8018/discusses/Q123 evidence

  - Need quick compressed understanding before returning to source evidence:
    Read summaries, then verify important claims with evidence.
      wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3/summary

  - Need bounded Agent-readable context around an object:
    Use pack only after choosing a located chunk or entity URI.
      wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/entity/Q162593 pack --budget 5000

  - Need more results from a paged response:
    Continue with the cursor returned by the previous command.
      wikigraph next <cursor>

When to read deeper:
  - URI details, scope/object routing, pagination, JSON, and JSONL:
    wikigraph help uri
  - Format inference, stdin/stdout, create/import, export, and transform:
    wikigraph help format
  - LLM, concurrency, and WikiSpine provider setup:
    wikigraph help config
  - Workers, cache, logs, workspaces, failures, and JSONL progress:
    wikigraph help runtime
